sentences.sContent: I hadn’t been to the city for 20 years and it was almost unrecognizable.
sentences.sCn: 我已经 20 年没有到过这座城市，几乎认不出来了。

synos.tran: 未被承认的；无法认出的

trans.tranCn: 未被承认的, 无法识别的
trans.tranOther: someone or something that is unrecognizable has changed or been damaged so much that you do not recognize them
